The Bay of Fundy is known for having the highest tidal range in the world.

And a time-lapse video that captures the rise and fall of the ice-capped tide at Hall’s Harbour in Nova Scotia, Canada, shows the natural wonder in all its beauty.

Three fishing boats in the video appear to be beached as day breaks and the large sweeping shadow is replaced by sunlight.

