Suddenly the tide begins to rise in the distance and as water rushes through to the harbour the boats begin to rock on the surface of the bay.

The surface remains frozen throughout the video, but a gap in the ice on the left shows water flooding onto the side of the bank as the level rises.

Before long the water has risen to be parallel with the harbour and the boats that were once grounded sit awkwardly on the top of the ice.

